                  </persName>
             (Police-constable G 171). I stopped the prisoner at the corner of Greville-street, Hatton-garden- I got this handkerchief from a young lady, in the prosecutor's presence: I saw the prisoner throw two handkerchiefs down, and I got another from him at the station.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never had the prosecutor's handkerchief in my possession; I did not throw any away- the gentleman raised his umbrella to strike me, and I ran away.</p>
